eyes of the Iksar, inclined to trust him because of<br>
what she'd just heard.  Indeed, the High Elves of<br>
Felwithe would kill Kreeden, and indeed, maybe<br>
kill her, if they found out that the two were in alliance<br>
and that they both wanted admittance to Felwithe!<br>
<br>
And yet...the fate of more than their lives was at stake.<br>
<br>
&quot;Innoruuk must be stopped,&quot; said Zatdatine firmly.  <br>
&quot;To stop him, we must take chances, and chances<br>
that entail not only our present ways of life and our<br>
comfortable, safe routines, but also our lives themselves.<br>
The Prince of Hate will not cease to hate, and destroy,<br>
unless there is something TO hate!  He will not stop<br>
with Kelethin.  Other cities shall fall to his wrath,<br>
unless some faithful strangers step in to fight him!<br>
Those strangers shall be you and me, Iksar, no<br>
matter if Cazic-Thule be offended or not!&quot; <br>
<br>
She slowly unsheathed her Dragoon Dirk and pricked<br>
her right index finger with it.  Three drops of blood<br>
fell onto the shell-like gray scales of the Iksar's hand. <br>
<br>
&quot;This is not the ritual of the High Elves, or even of their<br>
good-hearted and flighty cousins, the Fier'Dal, but<br>
we half-breeds have our own rituals!  These three<br>
drops of blood represent the three things I pledge to<br>
you:  loyalty, kindness, and service.  I will not stop<br>
fighting until both of us lie wounded, captured, or dead!&quot; <br>
<br>
She pressed the Iksar's hand gently into her own, letting<br>
the scales absorb her blood.  &quot;I will do as you ask!&quot;  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kreeden>Kreeden</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.badassbuddy.com/images/buddies/badassbuddy_com-hydros.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/20/03 11:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1008.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Enter : Faydwer</span><hr size=1> Kreeden nodded, taken back by such hospitailty and acceptance, wishing once more that everyone was so accepting in Norrath.  &quot;We must hurry then, the spires are within sight, let's go!&quot;  Kreeden cloaked himself in shadows once more, and ran with Zatdatines lovely rendition of Selo's songs, and within no time at all they were at the spires.<br>
<br>
They sat off to the edge of the spires, waiting for the right moment to jump in to the center, rather then to risk Kreeden being detected.  There was quite a few eager adventureres at the spires, talking excitedly about going to Faydwer to combat the evils, many talking mournfully of going to look for survivors and family.<br>
<br>
The scion announced that two minutes remained until teleportation began.  Kreeden and Zatdatine made their way, cautiously into the center, Zatdatine making sure not to pay Kreeden any attention, as paying attention to an invisible figure wouldn't look to good to the others.<br>
<br>
Within a few seconds, teleportation began, and nearly instantly they were dumped in a large pile in Greater Faydark.  The kinks of modern teleportation obiviously still had to be worked out.  The sky was somewhat reddish, and smoking still, from the trees of Kelethin and other areas.  There was a distinct smell of death in the air, and a smell Kreeden knew all to well from Cabilis, yet he couldn't remember exactly what it was.  <br>
<br>
Kreeden remained close to Zatdatine, tugging on her cloak to let her know he's still with her.  They followed a path eastward, which curved northward.  The smoke was getting thicker.  &quot;Up ahead is Felwhite, I have no idea of how strongly it may be guarded and it's best if you head up to the hill over eastward and wait, I'll come for you there once I've spoken to the King.  Kreeden nodded an invisible nod, and wished her well as they split ways for the first time since meeting, and Kreeden found a hill and began ordering his spellbook for the possible battles to come.  Off in the distance, a foul laughing could be heard snaking through the trees of Faydark. <p>&lt;center&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;red&quot;&gt; Kreeden - 60 Phantasmist Retired&lt;/font&gt;<br>
