meekly asked King Tearis Thex, &quot;What are you going<br>
to do with Kreeden, my Iksar companion on this quest?&quot; <br>
<br>
&quot;I've sent him to Crushbone,&quot; said Tearis purposefully.  <br>
&quot;I'm hoping the lizard can spy on the Orcs and tell me<br>
what their future battle plans are.  It seems to me that<br>
these simple-minded servants of Innoruuk are crucial<br>
to preventing further attacks on Faydwer.  We must<br>
find out what they're up to, before they strike again!&quot; <br>
<br>
&quot;Are you sure you didn't send him there to kill him?&quot;  <br>
Zatdatine knew how much the High Elves hated the<br>
residents of Cabilis. They were wicked in Tunare's eyes.<br>
<br>
&quot;Zatdatine, your words cut me straight to the core!&quot; <br>
the King cried. &quot;I am not offended, however, or worried<br>
that you've discovered my true motive. In this time of<br>
disaster, we must rely upon all our allies, scaled or no,<br>
in order to stop Innoruuk and his hateful minions. If the<br>
Iksar wants to fight, let him fight! Let him spy, also,<br>
for this is the task that I've set him to.  Now for yours...&quot;<br>
<br>
Zatdatine waited with baited breath for Tearis' words.<br>
<br>
&quot;Since you serve Veeshan, the Mother of All Wurms,<br>
then I send you out into the forests of Faydwer to call<br>
all the drakelings to war!  Surely, there are several <br>
young green dragons that are far too weak to stand<br>
alone in a battle and live, but with your help, even the<br>
youngest of drakelings will be able to aid us in our<br>
fight against the Prince of Hate!  Go now, and send<br>
word to all the Wurms that Veeshan is no longer our<br>
enemy! She is our ally now, as are all her servants!&quot; <br>
Tearis folded his arms across his blazing chest. <br>
<br>
&quot;Yes, Sire,&quot; said Zatdatine, kneeling before him again.<br>
&quot;I shall do my best to tell the drakelings of our cause!&quot; <br>
<br>
She ran out into the midst of the forest, drumming the <br>
Chant of Battle as she sang a war song in Dragon: <br>
<br>
&quot;Drakelings, Hate's destroyed your home,<br>
 Leaving you helpless to roam<br>
 In the wilds of this wood, <br>
 Where there's barely drink and food!<br>
<br>
 The Prince of Hate has gone too far<br>
 In his never-ending war<br>
 Against all forces of Good! <br>
 I hope this is understood! <br>
<br>
 All you Dragons, large and small,<br>
 Help us fight, O one and all!<br>
 I serve Veeshan, your dear Queen!<br>
 Come to me!  I'm Zatdatine!&quot;<br>
<br>
After her song was finished, Zatdatine was amazed to<br>
hear a furious flapping of leathery wings. All the dragons<br>
in the realm of the Greater Faydark came charging <br>
toward her, claws reared for battle and teeth bared for<br>
the fight!  &quot;Zatdatine, we come!&quot; they cried, some of<br>
them breathing fire in small orange puffs as they spoke.  <br>
&quot;Innoruuk has damaged us! We will do anything to<br>
support the fight for his downfall!&quot;  They hovered near.<br>
<br>
&quot;Good,&quot; smiled the Bard.  &quot;Head for the spires, and<br>
make sure no one stops you!  The travellers and fellow<br>
fighters there will not harm you if you tell them what's<br>
going on.&quot;  With a hiss goodbye, the Drakelings sped off.<br>
<br>
She returned to the King, her mission accomplished,<br>
expecting to hear his high praise, yet the concern on<br>
his pale face unnerved her.  &quot;What's wrong?&quot; she asked.<br>
<br>
&quot;Iksar,&quot; said the King.  &quot;He's been beaten and captured!&quot;<br>
<br>
Zatdatine cried, &quot;Take me to Kreeden!&quot; and a Paladin<br>
guard obliged, his silver armor ablaze.  Yet when the<br>
Half-Elf saw her scaled friend, he lay unconscious on<br>
the floor of his iron cell.  The Bard sang a song to <br>
comfort him while he recovered from his head wounds.<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kreeden>Kreeden</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.badassbuddy.com/images/buddies/badassbuddy_com-hydros.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/22/03 9:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1008.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Oww!  My head hurts!</span><hr size=1> Kreeden shut his eyes again and held them shut.  He wanted to shout in pain but did not want to startle his captors.  He reopened his eyes, the green robed figure had been replaced by a elvish appearing female, with a lute in hand, singing some sort of calming ballad.  Kreeden once more released his eyes to darkness, in his mind the clear picture of Zatdatine strumming notes on her lute.  Kreeden was lulled to sleep.<br>
<br>
When he awoke, he had been carefully placed in a fine bed, in a room by himself.  There was a bell on the stand next to the bed.  The floor and walls were of white marble, what most of the city was made of, or so Kreeden had read.<br>
<br>
Kreeden rang the bell, within seconds the High King and Zatdatine entered through the door.  The High King looked rather relieved to see Kreeden in this shape.<br>
<br>
&quot;What day is it?&quot;  Kreeden asked, impatiently, and trying to lift himself up, refusing help from the clerical aids.<br>
<br>
&quot;You left here two days ago...&quot; the High King said, then asking more purposefully, &quot;What do you have to report?&quot;<br>
<br>
Kreeden was sitting up fully now, he noticed the bandage on his arm, and a large one across the back of his head.  &quot;Let me think...&quot;  The King shot him an impatient look, yet one of understanding.  Here the King interrupted, &quot;Take your time, you're lucky that you Iksar have such an amazing regeneration, it would take even the finest of my guard a week to recover from the injuries you likely sustained.&quot;<br>
<br>
Kreeden absentmindly thanked him, and continued, &quot;We have six days until there is a large force from the spires, planar creatures of hate to invade and flank your forces while a divisionary offensive takes place at Crushbone.&quot;<br>
<br>
The Kings jaw started to droop a bit, and he regained his composure, though barely, saying, &quot;How.. how many?&quot;<br>
<br>
Kreeden shrugged, &quot;Hard to tell.  I'd estimate at least forty.  I've been to the Plane of Hate before, and the Plane of Fear as well.  Field trips for necromancy courses in Cabilis.  I have knowledge on any planar creature from those areas you may need.  Though I have a commending respect for your elven people, for allowing me to stay here, and a I respect your military for staging off invasions of Ambassador D'Vinn, I suggest an alliance with the gnomes and dwarves alike, and humans if possible, you need all the help you can get, especially if Innoruuk can figure out how to launch his larger planar dragons through the spires.&quot;<br>
<br>
The King thanked Kreeden immensely, confirmed that in five days the attack would occur, and left Kreeden to welcoming sleep.  Zatdatine stayed and strummed her lute, hoping her drakelings were successful. <p>&lt;center&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;red&quot;&gt; Kreeden - 60 Phantasmist Retired&lt;/font&gt;<br>
&lt;/b&gt;<br>
&lt;BR&gt;<br>
&lt;font color=&quot;blue&quot;&gt; Bladdes - 5 Warrior &lt;/font&gt;</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rhaxalygen>Rhaxalygen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 259<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/23/03 3:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1008.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Zatdatine's Second Task</span><hr size=1> King Tearis Thex was anxious to send both Zatdatine,<br>
the Veeshan Bard, and Kreeden, the new Iksar spy,<br>
back into service. The young Half-Elven girl's first <br>
mission had been thoroughly successful; more of the<br>
larger drakes, and even some full-grown dragons, were<br>
headed for the Spires. That accomplished, Tearis spoke: <br>
<br>
&quot;Girl, I want you to venture into the cities of Kaladim and<br>
Ak'anon. Send word to the Gnomes and the Dwarves that<br>
Innoruuk has laid siege to Kelethin, and we High Elves of<br>
Felwithe need their help fighting if we're not to die next!&quot; <br>
<br>
&quot;I will do as you ask, Sire,&quot; replied Zatdatine matter-of<br>
factly, &quot;yet I don't think I'm the best one to accomplish<br>
this task! Brell Serilis and Veeshan consider themselves enemies, so I don't think either a Dwarf or a Gnome would take kindly to an order from a servant of the Wurms!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Do not give them orders,&quot; advised Tearis Thex, &quot;but rather approach them humbly. Stress the importance<br>
of their help in our fight against Innoruuk. Remember,<br>
the Dwarves abhor anything evil, and the Gnomes do<br>
also, although some of them are slaves of Bertoxxulous.<br>
Go straight to the good clockwork, King Ak'anon, and<br>
tell him that both Felwithe and Kelethin are soon to be <br>
fully destroyed if the Gnomes and Dwarves don't help!&quot; <br>
<br>
&quot;Right!&quot; cried Zatdatine, and she sped away. <br>
<br>
Alerting King Kazon Stormhammer to the dangers ahead<br>
proved to be a rather difficult task, for Zatdatine had to sing one of her charisma-increasing carillons in order<br>
for the armored Dwarf to stop glowering at her dubiously.<br>
However, once the song was sung, King Stormhammer<br>
listened with undivided attention to the young Bard's warning. &quot;Brell help us all!&quot; he cried when her tale was<br>
done.  &quot;You tell that Thex of Felwithe that we'll fight <br>
and die, if that's what we ha' to do, in order to kill Hate!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Thank ye for your assistance!&quot; called the trembling Half-Elf as she raced out of Kaladim. The King of the Dwarves, mused Zatdatine, was not a bad sort if you<br>
kept singing your charisma song. Otherwise, he was <br>
rather a stubborn and hard-nosed old twit with a crown!<br>
Then, Zatdatine thought, the same could be said of King <br>
Tearis Thex, minus the Dwarven heritage!<br>
<br>
Ak'Anon proved to be far easier than Kaladim to enter. <br>
The Gnomes rarely emerged from their subterranean<br>
tunnels to mingle with the other races of Norrath, and<br>
since King Ak'Anon was not a Gnome himself, but<br>
a clockwork, the frightened emotions that Kazon had<br>
shown at her scary tidings was not present in the former.<br>
<br>
King Ak'Anon turned towards the young Bard with a mechanical whir. &quot;We will fight,&quot; he said in a monotone,  <br>
and then the Lord of the Gnomes said something that<br>
puzzled even himself: &quot;The Lord of Disease calls you!&quot;<br>
Instantly, King Ak'Anon exploded into a thousand bits,<br>
and the fiery forces of the blast chain-reacted through<br>
the tunnels of the Gnomish city one by one, destroying<br>
them all. Very systematic, at least for Bertoxxulous. <br>
<br>
The Gnomes of the Dark Reflection had allied with Hate.<br>
Zatdatine lay on the floor of the King's fragmented chamber, barely conscious of anything save the fleeing<br>
of several scared Gnomes. She closed her eyes, and<br>
everything faded to black. Was this the end, after all? <br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kreeden>Kreeden</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.badassbuddy.com/images/buddies/badassbuddy_com-hydros.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/23/03 5:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1008.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Recon</span><hr size=1> Kreeden awoke again, rang the bell next to his bed, and was promptly answered by a servant cleric.  The cleric checked the bandages covering Kreeden's wounds, which he himself had not seen clearly yet.  <br>
<br>
The cleric undressed the wounds, noting of the marvels of iksar regeneration, something new to Felwithe medical research.  Kreeden rolled his eyes around, &quot;I'm feeling much better, thank you.&quot;<br>
<br>
The cleric nodded, and dissappeared, leaving the stone door open.  Kreeden stood up, waited for the dizziness to subside, and exited the room.  He went right in the hallway, the room around the corner from the right had to have been well-lit, for the light was very bright, even from where Kreeden stood.<br>
<br>
Stumbling around the corner, bracing himself on the walls, Kreeden appeared in a vast room, with floors of sparkling marble and a cieling of the same.  <br>
<br>
&quot;Ah, our iksar has awoke.&quot;  the King said, somewhat cautiously.  &quot;I trust you'll make no sudden moves.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;What is this?  Are we not on friendly terms?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Hardly, I can use you for business and such, and you are here within Felwithe, as you requested.&quot;<br>
<br>
Kreeden let it slide, he could prove more useful and figured he would be granted more liberties as that came.  &quot;What of Zatdatine?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;She's on an errand, she left for Kaladim and Ak'anon two days ago.&quot;  That leaves three days to the invasion, Kreeden mentally noted.  The King continued, &quot;She should be back by now, scouts saw her enter Butcherblock Mountains by way of the small pass through the mountains, and they also saw her come back through, and enter the Lesser Faydark, here they lost track of her.&quot;<br>
<br>
Kreeden's eyes narrowed.  &quot;She was being stalked?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Aye, of course, you don't expect me to fully trust a half elf young girl traveling with an outcasted iksar, did you?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Trust seems to be hard to earn here.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Everyone has standards.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Do you have anything else for me to do?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Aye, I would like you to go back to Crushbone, claiming to have escaped, and tell them that our force will be completely centered on the northern flank, nearest Crushbone.  Maybe that way our size of our forces will be underestimated.&quot;<br>
<br>
Kreeden nodded, though he had other plans.<br>
<br>
Kreeden non-chalantly walked out of the city, under the ever-dubious eyes of the local militia and the towns-folk.<br>
<br>
Kreeden walked up the path towards Crushbone, completely knowledgeable of the stalkers behind him, sprinting through trees.  When Felwithe was out of earshot, Kreeden stopped and retrieved his spellbook from his pack.  The book hadn't been used in quite some while, he held his hand over the scroll for &quot;Summon Dead&quot;, and chanted outloud in iksar, something the stalkers could not understand.  He repeated this process for scrolls of &quot;Dooming Darkness&quot;, &quot;Words of Spirit&quot;, and &quot;Vampiric Curse&quot;.  He stood, mentally grasping where exactly the stalkers were located.  By closing his eyes and using superior concentration, he was able to detect one stalker behind him, on a tree branch, another was a bit ahead and to his left, behing a large tree, and a third was off to his left, hiding in the shadows.<br>
<br>
Kreeden released magic from his concentration and from the ground arose a minion for him to command, a brittle skeleton.  He reeled and fired a lifetap spell in the direction of the stalker in the tree.  It hit solidly, and instantly the other stalkers closed in on Kreeden for the kill.  The lifetap was not enough to kill, however it knocked the stalker off the tree, and though he landed safely, he had to gather his senses for a moment.  Kreeden sent his minion towards the stalker that was behind him, charging him was the other two stalkers, the right-most one Kreeden casted Dooming Darkness on, slowing his movement and spiritually slowly harming him.  The other stalker charging him Kreeden casted Vampiric Curse upon.  The stalker was reeling in pain, clutching his chest.  With both of the stalkers following him, he made his way to his minion, who was in a dead-lock fight with the third stalker.  When all were in the same general vicinity, Kreeden let loose with an immensely powerful spell.<br>
<br>
Words of Spirit was channeled through Kreeden's fingers, and all three stalkers fell dead immediately.  Kreeden allowed a minute to rest and backtracked quickly southward, past Felwithe, avoiding the guards, and into Lesser Faydark.  Here he cautiously traversed the right side of the mountain, and in no time came to the Steamfront mountain range.  Here, Ak'anon was clearly visible, even though an underground city.  Following the gears and contraptions, he made his way into Ak'anon, resisting the urge to stop and investigate some of the trinkets, and keeping one eye out for Zatdatine.  <br>
<br>
Upon entering Ak'anon, he forgot of his unacceptance in the land of Faydwer, and he was promptly knocked unconcious and drug to a mechanically engineered cage.  Here he awoke, and Zatdatine was in a cage across from him, her cage very much like his.  She was still out cold, or so he thought, however Kreeden was wide awake and aware of his surroundings. <p>&lt;center&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;red&quot;&gt; Kreeden - 60 Phantasmist Retired&lt;/font&gt;<br>
&lt;/b&gt;<br>
&lt;BR&gt;<br>
&lt;font color=&quot;blue&quot;&gt; Bladdes - 5 Warrior &lt;/font&gt;</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rhaxalygen>Rhaxalygen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 260<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/23/03 8:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1008.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> The Dark Reflection--Is It Darker than Hate? </span><hr size=1> Veeshan, and also the Clerics and Shadow Knights of<br>
the Dark Reflection in Ak'anon, had other plans for the<br>
wandering Bard and the Necromancer Iksar besides death. Evah Xokez, the leader of the Gnomish Clerics<br>
of Bertoxxulous, watched over her captives with a <br>
triumphant smile on her face. The Dark Reflection had destroyed the city--indeed, they had survived the very blast they had caused--for the Plague Lord had spared their lives in exchange for their allegiance and service!<br>
<br>
&quot;Good morning,&quot; Evah chirped to the Iksar as he struggled against the bars of his mechanical cage. <br>
&quot;I trust you've been feeling well.&quot; <br>
<br>
&quot;Actually, I feel somewhat like gnoll dung,&quot; Kreeden hissed, &quot;and this seems to be because of you!  Why<br>
have you caged us here, and why, if you wanted us<br>
dead, didn't you leave us to expire among the rubble?!&quot; <br>
<br>
&quot;I did NOT want you dead,&quot; replied Evah huskily.  &quot;The <br>
Plague Lord prefers his servants living, if diseased. The skeleton pets he employs are only creations of his Necromancers, and Bertoxxulous loves a living servant<br>
far more than a dead one!  The dead, after all, don't have minds of their own.  They act just like live beasts!&quot; <br>
<br>
&quot;If you didn't want us dead,&quot; growled the Iksar, &quot;then I<br>
suggest you revise your assumption that we will serve<br>
you.  The Bard, after all, pledges her loyalty to Veeshan, the Queen of all Wurms, and I already have a master,<br>
Cazic-Thule!  Not that I'm so loyal to him right now, but at least he demands service from me to him alone!&quot;  <br>
<br>
&quot;I pity you,&quot; sighed the Gnome Cleric.  &quot;You suppress your evil desires, and for what?  All to be scorned and<br>
rejected by the races of Norrath, and killed on first sight if you ever take one step into a Good town!  Freeport, a haven for Evil, shall even slaughter you if you go there! <br>
Come join us, Iksar, and help your master, Thule, aid<br>
Innoruuk, the Prince of Hate.  Evil shall soon conquer!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Rrrurrrurgghhrrrss!&quot;  This was a very bad Iksarian word.  <br>
<br>
&quot;Shhh,&quot; smiled Evah.  &quot;The Bard's waking up.&quot; <br>
<br>
Zatdatine stirred in her cage, barely noticing the shards<br>
of metal stuck into her skin like splinters.  A greenish,<br>
cool underground cave was where she seemed to be.<br>
<br>
&quot;Huh?&quot; asked the young hybrid girl, gasping in pain.  &quot;What happened?  What's going on?!&quot;  Her heart raced.  She remembered a king--yes, a clockwork king--and then a violent and fiery explosion...<br>
<br>
&quot;We set an explosive device inside King Ak'anon,&quot; the <br>
Cleric explained with a smirk.  &quot;That pathetic, rusty old<br>
defective clockwork exploded, and now all of Ak'anon<br>
is ours, a sacrifice to our new ally, the Prince of Hate!&quot; <br>
<br>
&quot;How could you?!&quot; cried Zatdatine.  &quot;AAAAHHH!&quot; <br>
The shards of metal were digging into her skin, and<br>
the Bardess was too weak to move or to pull them out.<br>
<br>
&quot;Pain is a catalyst for change, milady,&quot; Evah said gently.<br>
&quot;A change of allegiance, for one thing, from the forces of Light, or at least Neutrality, to the forces of Darkness. <br>
Another change it will effect is a change from your worship of Veeshan to the worship of Bertoxxulous. You'll be the first Bard to do so!&quot; Evah was elated. <br>
<br>
&quot;Never!&quot; cried the fearless girl.  &quot;I shall never worship<br>
Bertoxxulous or assist the Prince of Hate, and I--aah--HISSSSSSSSSS--!&quot; This last gasp was of pure agony.<br>
<br>
&quot;Atropos is upon you,&quot; said Evah Xokez. &quot;The third Fate,<br>
or the one who holds the Shears of Death, is soon to<br>
cut your thread. Unless you serve the Plaguebringer, and us, the life which gentle Lachesis has measured<br>
will shortly slip past us into the Void.  What will it be?&quot; <br>
<br>
&quot;Death!&quot; cried the Bard, and she passed out again.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page  <b>1</b> <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.showMessageRange?topicID=1008.topic&start=21&stop=22>2</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.showPrevMessage?topicID=1008.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.showNextMessage?topicID=1008.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1008.topic&index=20><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/classic/addReply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.threadControl?topicID=1008.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1008.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1008.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email notification of replies"> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies</a> <br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub94.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="firionaviefrm1">Firiona Vie Gene